===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}}, alteration of earlier {{term|hendi||handy, skillful|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hendig|hendiġ|skillful|lang=ang}} (as in {{term|listhendig|listhendiġ|skilled in art|lang=ang}}), from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|handugaz||handy, skillful, nimble|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{recons|handuz||hand|lang=gem-pro}}, equivalent to {{suffix|hand|y|lang=-}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gml|-}} {{term|handich||skillful, apt|lang=gml}}, {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|handec|lang=gmh}}, {{term|hendec||manual, hand-held|lang=gmh}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|hǫndugr||sc=Latinx|efficient|lang=non}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|𐌷𐌰𐌽𐌳𐌿𐌲𐍃||tr=handugs|wise, clever|lang=got|sc=Goth}}.

